definition.value: A myo-inositol monophosphate derivative that is 1D-myo-inositol substituted at position 1 by an sn-glycero-3-phospho group.
A straight-chain fatty acid anion and the conjugate base of 6-oxohexanoic acid, formed by deprotonation of the carboxylic acid group.

A series of oligoglycosylceramides having beta-D-galactosyl-(1-3)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1-3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1-4)-beta-D-glucose as the tetrasaccharide sequence root. The oligosaccharide portion can be elongated in a linear or branched form.

A series of oligoglycosylceramides having beta-D-galactosyl-(1-4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1-3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1-4)-beta-D-glucose as the tetrasaccharide sequence root. The oligosaccharide portion can be elongated in a linear or branched form.
A racemate composed of equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-goitrin. It is an antithyroid agent found in cabbage, rutabaga, turnip, and brassicaceous weeds.
A member of the class of oxazolidines that is 1,3-oxazolidine substituted by sulfanylidene and ethenyl groups at positions 2 and 5, respectively.
A 5-ethenyl-1,3-oxazolidine-2-thione that has R-configuration. It is a constituent of a traditional Chinese herbal medicine, Radix isatidis.
A 4-hexen-3-one in which the double bond adopts a trans-configuration.
A dipeptide comprising of beta-alanine and 3-methyl-L-histidine units.
A 4-hexen-3-one in which the double bond adopts a cis-configuration.
A lysophosphatidic acid in which the acyl group (position not specified) contains 17 carbons and no double bonds.
Major microspecies at pH 7.3
A lysophosphatidylethanolamine in which the acyl group (position not specified) contains 17 carbons and 1 double bond.
A lysophosphatidylethanolamine in which the acyl group (position not specified) contains 18 carbons and 4 double bonds.
A lysophosphatidylglycerol in which the acyl group has a fully saturated C16 chain and is attached to the glycero moiety at either position 1 or 2.
A lysophosphatidylglycerol in which the acyl group has a fully saturated C17 chain and is attached to the glycero moiety at either position 1 or 2.
A lysophosphatidylglycerol in which the acyl group has a fully saturated C18 chain and is attached to the glycero moiety at either position 1 or 2.
A lysophosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol in which the remaining acyl group (position not specified) contains 18 carbons and 4 double bonds.
A lysophosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol in which the remaining acyl group (position not specified) contains 14 carbons and 0 double bonds.
A lysophosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol in which the remaining acyl group (position not specified) contains 15 carbons and 0 double bonds.
A lysophosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol in which the remaining acyl group (position not specified) contains 16 carbons and 0 double bonds.
A lysophosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol in which the remaining acyl group (position not specified) contains 17 carbons and 0 double bonds.
A lysophosphatidylserine in which the remaining acyl group (position not specified) contains 14 carbons and 0 double bonds.
